<subSubSection id="C369B08A227EFFABA9C21195FED0AE4E" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227EFFABA9C21195FD0FA8A5" blockId="7.[178,1236,494,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">
Distribution: from northern 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAB561195FD78A825" box="[627,738,494,521]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Germany</collectingCountry>
south to south-west 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAADD1195FBD1A825" box="[1016,1099,494,521]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">France</collectingCountry>
, and from 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA9971275FE8EA805" box="[178,276,526,553]" name="Belgium" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Belgium</collectingCountry>
eastwards through central and southern Europe (
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAA7A1275FC48A805" box="[863,978,526,553]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAAFB1275FBAEA805" box="[990,1076,526,553]" name="Poland" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Poland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAD1A1275FBECA805" box="[1087,1142,526,553]" name="Italy" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Italy</collectingCountry>
, former 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA9971255FEAFA865" box="[178,309,558,585]" name="Serbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
) to 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA84F1255FDB3A865" box="[362,553,558,585]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAB1D1255FD07A865" box="[568,669,558,585]" name="Slovakia" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Slovakia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAB8E1255FC8CA865" box="[683,790,558,585]" name="Hungary" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAA031255FC09A865" box="[806,915,558,585]" name="Romania" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAA861255FB9FA865" box="[931,1029,558,585]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and central part of European 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA8771235FE04A845" box="[338,414,590,617]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABA8951235FDADA845" author="Peck, L. V." box="[432,567,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="11 - 230" refId="ref4662" refString="Peck, L. V. 1988. Family Syrphidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L., eds. Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera, 8 (Syrphidae - Conopidae). Elsevier Science Publishers &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Amsterdam, Budapest, 11 - 230." type="book chapter" year="1988">Peck, 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABAB631235FC12A845" author="Holinka, J. &amp; Mazanek, L." box="[582,904,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="60 - 66" refId="ref4283" refString="Holinka, J. &amp; Mazanek, L. 1997. Syrphidae. In: Chvala, M., ed. Check List of Diptera (Insecta) of the Czech and Slovak Republics. Karolinum Press, Charles University, Prague, 60 - 66." type="book chapter" year="1997">Holinka &amp; Mazánek, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABAAB21235FB87A845" author="Toth, S." box="[919,1053,590,617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="5 - 408" refId="ref5241" refString="Toth, S. 2011. Magyarorszag zengolegy faunaja (Diptera: Syrphidae) [Hoverfly fauna of Hungary (Diptera: Syrphidae)]. e-ActaNaturaliaPannonica, Supplementum 1, 5 - 408. http: // epa. oszk. hu / 01900 / 01957 / 00012 / pdf / EPA 01957 _ e-acta _ nat _ pannon _ suppl _ 1 _ 2011. pdf" type="journal article" year="2011">Tóth, 2011</bibRefCitation>
; Speight, 2017; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABA9971215FEE7A8A5" author="Mielczarek, L." box="[178,381,622,649]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="2009 - 2018" refId="ref4471" refString="Mielczarek, L. 2018 (2009 - 2018). List of species Syrphidae of Poland (Diptera, Syrphidae). http: // syrphidae. insects. pl / checklist. php? lang = en" type="book chapter" year="2018">Mielczarek, 2018</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA8B51215FE6AA8A5" box="[400,496,622,649]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(first record).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227EFFABA9C212F5FC74A9A5" blockId="7.[178,1236,494,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">
Diagnosis. It easily differs from the other European species of the genus by the distinctly haired eyes, the hairs longer than the diameter of the anterior ocellus (in other species, the eye hairs very sparse, no hairs longer than the diameter of the anterior ocellus). 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227EFFABA9971295FE52A924" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[178,456,750,776]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetum">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227EFFABA9971295FE52A924" box="[178,456,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Xanthogramma laetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227EFFABAB501294FC26A925" authority="(Loew, 1854)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[629,956,750,777]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginale">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227EFFABAB501294FC8BA924" box="[629,785,750,776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">X. marginale</emphasis>
(Loew, 1854)
</taxonomicName>
only in having yellow transverse fasciae on tergite 3, but can be separated from it by the tergite 2 wider than long, tergite 4 with a transverse yellow fascia and the alula entirely covered by microtrichia (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227EFFABA9971334FEDDA944" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[178,327,846,872]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginale">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227EFFABA9971334FEDDA944" box="[178,327,846,872]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">X. marginale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergite 2 longer than wide, tergite 4 with a pair of transverse yellow marks and the alula extensively bare) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABA8D51315FD2FA9A5" author="Violovitsh, N. A." box="[496,693,878,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="90 - 106" refId="ref5341" refString="Violovitsh, N. A. 1975. A short review of the Palaearctic species of the genus Xanthogramma Schiner (Diptera, Syrphidae). In: Cherepanov, A. I., ed. Taxonomy and ecology of Siberian animals (New and little-known Siberian fauna species, Vol. 9). Nauka, Novosibirsk, 90 - 106." type="book chapter" year="1975">Violovitsh, 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227EFFABABE51315FC7BA9A5" author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P." box="[704,993,878,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" pagination="1 - 139" refId="ref5117" refString="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. 2017. StN keys for the identification of the European species of various genera of Syrphidae 2017. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 99, 1 - 139. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin." type="journal article" year="2017">Speight &amp; Sarthou, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227EFFABA9C213D7FED0AE4E" blockId="7.[178,1236,940,1122]" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">
We are very grateful to Volodymyr Roshko (Uzhhorod National University, Uzhhorod), for his kind assistance in organizing a collecting trip to Zakarpattia Region in 2017. We also thank Valery Korneyev (Institute of Zoology of NAS of 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABA8A61399FE4EA9D4" box="[387,468,994,1016]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227EFFABA8F91399FD91A9D4" box="[476,523,994,1016]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
) for valuable scientific and editorial comments. The authors are grateful to Alex Gumovsky (Institute of Zoology of NAS of 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAB5B1387FD55AE3E" box="[638,719,1020,1042]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227EFFABABF21387FC9CAE3E" box="[727,774,1020,1042]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
) for the opportunity to use the Leica microscope system for imaging. The authors thank Tore Nielsen (Sandness, 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227EFFABAA39146CFCF1AE01" box="[796,875,1047,1069]" name="Norway" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Norway</collectingCountry>
) for his valuable comments on 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227EFFABADBE146CFED9AE6B" authorityName="Vockeroth" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nielseni">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227EFFABADBE146CFED9AE6B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="248">Platycheirus nielseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The authors would like to thank two anonymous reviewers for their valuable contributions to the manuscript.
</paragraph>
